@notice Welcome to the Community contract. For each community
 there will be one contract like this being deployed by
 ImpactMarket contract. This enable us to save tokens on the
 contract itself, and avoid the problems of having everything
 in one single contract. Each community has it's own members and
 and managers.
@dev Allow community managers to add other managers.
@dev Allow community managers to remove other managers.
@dev Allow community managers to add beneficiaries.
@dev Allow community managers to lock beneficiaries.
@dev Allow community managers to unlock locked beneficiaries.
@dev Allow community managers to remove beneficiaries.
@dev Allow beneficiaries to claim.
@dev Allow community managers to edit community variables.
@dev Allow community managers to lock community claims.
@dev Allow community managers to unlock community claims.
@dev Method called by a bot that deposits cUSD to earn interest.
@dev Migrate funds in current community to new one.

addBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to add beneficiaries.

addManager(address).details: Allow community managers to add other managers.

constructor.details: Constructor with custom fields, choosen by the community.

params._claimAmount: Base amount to be claim by the benificiary.
params._firstManager: Comminuty's first manager. Will be able to add others.
params._incrementInterval: Increment interval used in each claim.
params._maxClaim: Limit that a beneficiary can claim at once.
params._previousCommunityContract: previous smart contract address of community.

depoistAndEarn().details: Method called by a bot that deposits cUSD to earn interest.

edit(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Allow community managers to edit community variables.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

lock().details: Allow community managers to lock community claims.

lockBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to lock beneficiaries.

migrateFunds(address,address).details: Migrate funds in current community to new one.

removeBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to remove beneficiaries.

removeManager(address).details: Allow community managers to remove other managers.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

unlock().details: Allow community managers to unlock community claims.

unlockBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to unlock locked beneficiaries.
